li>This is a graduate course in scientific computing created and taught by <a href=\"http://colorfulengineering.org/\">Oliver Serang</a> in 2014, which covers topics in computer science and statistics with applications from biology. The course is designed top-down, starting with a problem and then deriving a variety of solutions from scratch.</li>\n<li>Topics include memoization, recurrence closed forms, string matching (sorting, hash tables, radix tries, and suffix tries), dynamic programming (e.g. Smith-Waterman and Needleman-Wunsch), Bayesian statistics (e.g. the envelope paradox), graphical models (HMMs, Viterbi, junction tree, belief propagation), FFT, and the probabilistic convolution tree.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/user/fillwithlight/videos\">Lecture videos on Youtube</a> and for direct <a href=\"http://mlecture.uni-bremen.de/ml/index.php?option=com_content&#x26;view=article&#x26;id=233\">download</a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2015-05-22T07:55:01.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"lvwzhen/tools","categoryHTML":"<h3>Favicon</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.favicon.cc/\">favicon.cc</a></li>","updatedAt":"2015-05-22T02:21:22.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"lvwzhen/tools","categoryHTML":"<h3>Favicon</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://iconogen.com/\">iconogen</a></li>","updatedAt":"2015-05-22T02:21:22.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"lvwzhen/tools","categoryHTML":"<h3>CSS</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://spritegen.website-performance.org/\">css spritegen</a></li>","updatedAt":"2015-05-22T02:21:22.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"lvwzhen/tools","categoryHTML":"<h3>CSS</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://csssprites.com/\">csssprites</a></li>","updatedAt":"2015-05-22T02:21:22.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"afonsopacifer/awesome-flexbox","categoryHTML":"<h2>Cross Browser</h2><h4>Articles</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://imasters.com.br/front-end/css/normalizando-bugs-no-flexbox-em-diversos-navegadores/?trace=1519021197&#x26;source=single\">Nor